 the\nGalactic value, the $E(B-V)$/$N_{\\rm H}$ value for F2M 0830+3759 is lower than\nthe Galactic standard, consistent with the paradigm that the dust resides on\ngalactic scales while the X-ray reprocessing gas originates within the\ndust-sublimation zone of the broad-line-region. The X-ray and 6.1$\\mu$m\nluminosities of these red quasars are consistent with the empirical relations\nderived for high-luminosity, unobscured quasars, extending the parameter space\nof obscured AGN previously observed by NuSTAR to higher luminosities.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 10 Feb 2016 21:00:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-04-06"}
